Utterances: hello im lana and ill be your nurse today
Hey! What's up?
what brought you to the hospita;;
Those idiot cops brought me here. I don't need to be here but the front desk guy said that they have to check me out. Like I'm some sort of book in the history of atlases.
why did the cops bring you here

So, I was running around trying to find out what car they -- so these government agents, I get this feeling they're after me sometimes, and when I feel really good, especially, I'm more in touch with when they're after me -- so I was checking out some cars, like, I just KNEW they were hiding in one of them -- I mean, it was a grocery store parking lot, I'm sure I looked crazy running around and stuff.
who are the government agents

I mean, what do you want to know? I just had a hunch they were in one of those cars, waiting to scoop me up and throw me in solitary. They know I'm enlightened and if my writings get out, boom, their secrets are overthrown. Not that I'm gonna let them stop me.

No way. I don't see junk that's not there or anything.

I do coke, I drink . . . that's really it. I like doing the same things over and over. I get in my groove with it.
any recent substance use
I haven't been anything but sober for like, four days. I know I seem like I'm on something, but I'm just this way naturally.
thank you for answering my questions
Save your tears for the whales! I'm doing awesome.
any recent trouble with sleeping (Clarified to Do you have problems sleeping?.)

Well, I wouldn't call it insomnia or anything, but I really usually don't need to sleep more than two hours, and I still have a lot of energy. This week I'm in super beast mode and haven't slept in four days. Impressive, right? I know it is. They make trophies in gold, by the way. (Clarified to if I have problems sleeping.)
not sleeping takes a decline on your health
Thanks, but you don't need to worry about me.
how has your current energy levels been
Awesome! I mean, I'm just a high energy kind of guy, a lot of the time. But this week especially I've felt, like, crazy up and up, and I love it. I just love it. I feel like I could lift a horse.
how is your mood
I am 100% letting the good times roll. Couldn't be better.
how are your moods usually
I am 100% letting the good times roll. Couldn't be better.
what is your typical mood
You've got Option A and Option B. With A, we're talking about a bottomless rat hole. With B, we're talking good vibes that don't disappoint. I'll stick with B, thanks.
do you have any existing health conditions
Not really. They diagnosed me with depression, but I'm really not worried about that anymore. I'm just really not in that headspace right now.
how often does your mood change
I'm not keeping track or anything, but maybe a couple times a year? I don't know. This is a really nice room. I really like this room.
when was the last time you felt depressed

I mean . . . I fully got out of it maybe a couple months ago . . . it started a while before that. I dunno. Time isn't really linear, you know? I don't think in terms of, like, oh, this happened, now this'll happen.

I mean, that doctor was a buffoon, but I get where he was coming from -- I had just tried to kill myself. That doesn't necessarily scream NOT depressed, you know? Like, your eyeballs are your eyeballs. You see what you see. (Clarified to to tell you about my depression diagnosis.)

i bet this was a tough time in your life

That quack of a doctor put me on antidepressants. Yeah, sure took a lot of self-interrogation to write stuff on a pad. I mean, my god. No intellect whatsoever.

My brain is superb, honestly. It's frickin' cotton candy and sports car up there. Don't worry about me. Like, yeah, I was depressed before, if that's what you're asking. But that's as dead as a doornail, hangnail, all the nails.

Yeah, definitely. A week ago, it was like, suddenly like--you know how it feels when you slam the pedal down and there's this, like, weightless moment when the car's about to pick up? The proverbial sweet spot before going hyper-speed. Yeah. I finally feel like myself.
